parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump control module can cause the fuel pump to run continuously, resulting in a drained battery and/or a no-start condition, or cause a loss of motive power while the vehicle is in motion, which can increase the risk of a crash causing injury and/or damage to property.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops receiving gas and starts coasting
the vehicle stops working in the middle of traffic
the fuel pump runs continuously
the battery drains
the vehicle is unable to start
the vehicle loses motive power while in motion.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing the fuel pump control module can cause the driver to continue driving a potentially dangerous vehicle, increasing the risk of a crash causing injury and/or damage to property.
symptoms: The driver receives notification of the recall but the part is unavailable
the dealer is unable to repair the vehicle
the manufacturer is unaware of the issue
the driver is forced to continue driving the vehicle without a repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump and push start ignition can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, which can increase the risk of a crash causing injury and/or damage to property.
symptoms: The push start ignition does not respond while turning the vehicle off
the vehicle stalls or does not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the gas pump to shut off every few seconds, making it difficult to fill the tank, which can cause inconvenience and delay.
symptoms: The gas pump clicks off every few seconds
the tank takes a long time to fill
the gas pump shuts off frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clock spring can cause the airbag light to come on, rendering the airbag system inoperable, and potentially leading to a lack of warning in the event of an accident. Additionally, the failure can also cause the horn to malfunction, increasing the risk of accidents due to the inability to warn other drivers.
symptoms: The airbag light comes on
the horn does not work
the audio controls on the steering wheel stop working
a noise comes out of the wheel when turning
and the steering panel does not function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The Takata airbag recall has left many owners without a functioning airbag system, putting them at risk in the event of an accident. The lack of available parts and unclear timelines for repair have caused frustration and concern among owners.
symptoms: None
as this issue is related to the recall and lack of repair rather than a specific symptom.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clock spring can cause the airbags to be disabled, leading to a significant safety risk in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag sensor light comes on
the horn does not work
electrical components on the wheel do not work
all airbags are disabled
the steering power fails
and the computer system malfunctions.
